author: Journal Inquirer Staff
title: Manchester enjoys resurgence
text:
Manchester enjoys resurgence By Journal Inquirer Staff Journal Inquirer | 0 comments 
For the Tolland High girls cross country team, it was business as usual. 
For the Manchester High boys cross country team, it was a case of turning back the clock to a day when the Indians were a formidable program. 
Led by a seventh place finish from Brian Coyne, Manchester won the Boys Seeded Race team championship with 186 points — just two points ahead of second-place Guilford at the Wickham Invitational in Manchester on Saturday. Thomas Kropp, Joe Pearl, Tim Rowe, James Lee, Tavaughn Webber, and Kyle Smith comprised the Manchester team that captured the title.
